content: That's a common reaction to Holden - he can be relatable in his feelings of alienation and disillusionment with the world around him, but his actions can be frustrating and even self-destructive at times. Some readers interpret Holden's behavior as a symptom of mental illness or trauma, while others see him as a typical teenager struggling to navigate the complexities of growing up. Regardless of one's interpretation of Holden's character, it's clear that his story has resonated with many readers over the years.
